Yes, I kind of see what you mean, yoric. After all, that's how all [DATA EXPUNGED] works: your clearance is high enough to receive access to the article but not to find out the grisly details.

I don't believe this article supplements the rest of the site. I believe it works best as a first article, before you've been spoiled by the other SCPs and are interested mainly in interesting or creepy effects. The style and tone of the SCP article itself is worth a lot in impressing first-time readers: more than established users give it credit for. This article relies totally on the Foundation concept and not at all upon an interesting subject.

I'll say it again. As an SCP, it's terrible. As an example of the genre, it's great. Which is more important?

Also, NekoChris: if your'e going to take that stance, why redact anything at all, if no articles are being released to the public? It makes sense that only part of a sensitive article would be revealed to a reader of insufficient clearance, right?







